cat > README.md <<'EOF'
# FLTWHT Fulfillment Bridge

Middleware to route FLTWHT orders from eBay and the static site into CustomCat fulfillment.

## Goal

Bridge unsupported sales channels into CustomCat fulfillment:
- eBay orders -> CustomCat
- FLTWHT.com static-site + Stripe orders -> CustomCat

## Current status

This repo has:
- real Stripe signature verification code
- checkout.session -> internal order transformation
- CustomCat CSV export in CustomCat's documented manual-upload column format
- eBay auth/order-fetch stub with exact operator credential requirements
- dry-run CustomCat submission path

## Endpoints

- `GET /health`
- `POST /webhooks/stripe`
- `POST /jobs/ebay-sync`
- `POST /admin/export-customcat-csv`

## CustomCat CSV format

The CSV export now uses CustomCat's documented headers:
- `OrderId`
- `LineItemId`
- `Quantity`
- `SKU`
- `ProductId`
- `ProductName`
- `Color`
- `Size`
- `DesignPosition`
- `ShipToFirstName`
- `ShipToLastName`
- `ShipToAddress`
- `ShipToAddress2`
- `ShipToCity`
- `ShipToZip`
- `ShipToState`
- `ShipToCountry`
- `ShipToPhone`
- `ShippingMethod`
- `CustomerEmail`

## Tests

- `test/stripe-webhook.test.js`
- sample Stripe event payload in `samples/stripe-checkout-session-completed.json`

## Important blockers

- This environment currently has no working `node` binary in shell, so CLI test execution is blocked here.
- CustomCat product/variant IDs are still `TBD` until catalog-specific IDs are gathered from CustomCat.
- eBay requires operator credentials:
  - `EBAY_CLIENT_ID`
  - `EBAY_CLIENT_SECRET`
  - `EBAY_REFRESH_TOKEN`
- CustomCat API still needs account-side credential verification before real dry-run request wiring can be verified.
